narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I enjoyed the in-class participation and the fact that the professor tried to get everyone to enjoy the class.

strengths: cool content, especially for the math-interested
weakness: class revolves a lot around solving seemingly arbitrary problems without any justification for their importance or even why certain methods work. Not asking for formal proofs, but maybe some intuition as to why some methods work to solve certain problems. The explorations are gone in theory, but are actually more annoying than anything. Should be due later.
loved cheat sheet idea, and peer tutoring was very effective
The strengths are that we get practice problems to learn from. The weakness is that the class material doesnt always cover techniques we need for psets or exams.
This class taught calculus concepts very well and easy to understand. I was never struggling to understand a concept even after reading through my textbook and asking questions to my professor.
I think the exams are the right level of challenging and the course was well-organized. I was not a huge fan of the learning strategies or calculus story requirements on Canvas.
